<br />
<CENTER><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: red"><a name=petexp></a>Pets and Experience</span></span></CENTER>
<br />
Originally posted by <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/Forum1/HTML/000594.html" target="_blank">Absor</a>
<br />

<br />
Here are the basic rules, along with some examples - 
<br />

<br />
Situation 1 - You are soloing and you have a summoned pet-
<br />
* If you do any damage to the monster at all, you get all of the experience. 
<br />
* If you don't do any damage to the monster, the pet gets 75% of the experience.
<br />

<br />
Situation 2 - You are in a group and you have a summoned pet-
<br />
* If you or your group do any damage to the monster at all, your group gets all of the experience.
<br />
* If you or your group don't do any damage to the monster, the pet gets 75% of the experience.
<br />

<br />
Damage shields count as neutral damage; Neither you nor your pet get credit for damage done by a damage shield.
<br />

<br />
If your pet dies or is reclaimed mid-battle, all damage done by it is considered zero for experience purposes.
<br />

<br />
It makes no difference if your pet gets the killing blow or not.
<br />

<br />
[<a href=#magepettop>Return to Top</a>]
<br />

<br />
<HR>
<br />

<br />
<CENTER><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: red"><a name=pettoys></a>Pet Weapons, Armor, and Buffs</span></span></Center>
<br />

<br />
Starting at level 1, Magicians have the potential to summon weapons and armor for their pets. Magicians also have the ability to damage shield their pets for additional damage towards enemies and monsters.
<br />

<br />
Pets will use almost all droppable items given to them, with few restrictions. Pets also do not follow recommended levels, but they do follow effect levels for weapon procs and such.
<br />

<br />
Lower level pets that do not dual wield will equip two-handed weapons; pets that dual wield will not equip two-handed weapons but will equip two one-handed weapons. Any weapon given to a pet with a higher damage than the pet's innate melee will boost the pet's attack power to that level. Also, weapons that are Magical in nature will imbue lower level pets with the ability to hit Magical creatures (and on a side note, all Magician summoned weapons are Magical). Pets are unaffected by the weapon type of weapons, be it hand-to-hand, slashing, blunt, or piercing.
<br />

<br />
Pets are not affected by required levels for spells. Higher level spells that are cast on the pet will affect the pet regardless of what level the pet actually is.
<br />

<br />
<P class=header4>Pet-Usable Summoned Weapons
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">*All summoned weapons are Magical</span>
