			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the absolute best way to test a pets regen is to duel somebody, nuke the pet and start a timer.  Stop the timer when the pet is full HP and record the damage done in the nuke, and how long it took to get to full HP.  The more damage per nuke, the more accurate the result.
<br />

<br />
The reason that test is probably best, is that it makes no assumptions on what the pets HP is, it simply see's how much damage was done, and times how long it takes to heal.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">EDIT:</span>  Ran some tests!
<br />

<br />
Ok I just logged in and ran some tests.  My results were the same as yours.  All the PoP pets seemed to have between 260 and 280 HP/tic regen.  Now I'm confused, becuase when I tested it before<span style="font-weight: bold"> I KNOW </span>I got 170 HP/tic regen.  I have the notes from the old tests still scribbled on some paper here on my desk.  The only thing I can conclude is at some point between LDoN coming out, and now they seem to have changed HP regen on the DPoC focused pets.  I'm guessing it was the same time they changed Manifest Elements.
<br />

<br />
Says right here on my notes, nukes landed for 2k, took about 72 seconds to regen.  73 on another test, 71 on another test.  I tested all 4 PoP pets and they were all consistant.  But the test I just did online was the same again for all pets, but the HP regen value was about 260-280 per tic just like what I have recently observed on the Epic pet.
<br />

<br />
BTW, I got about 5283 again for DPoC Rathe's Son, and I ran 3 tests on the same DPoC ward.  Each test put his HP regen square between 260 and 280. but his HP on each test was different.  One was 4096, another was 4340, another was 4534.  Makes me think the results are crap since they are inconsistant, but the regen clocked in pretty constant.  If I subtract 1 tic of % HP from the 4534 result and recalculate it comes out to 4128.  So I'm guessing there are times when the pet gets a tic of regen before the pets HP number is reported to the client and that is throwing off results some.
<br />

<br />
I had the wizard whom was helping me dispell the Child of Ro then nuke.  I'm not totally positive if his nuke went off before the CoR re self buffed, but the wizzy nuked CoR for 2696 and CoR was at 12%.  CoR was regenning 10-11% a tic.  Which again worked out to about 280/tic.  I really want to stress the point that in my earlier tests, the CoR pet seemed to have 4100 HP unbuffed.  He was NOT regenning 10-11% before when I did the tests with Fricken the mage.  I really think a recent patch changed the SoR's base HP and the regen given to pets from the DPoC
<br />

<br />
I'll go update my thread in the library about DPoC now.
<br />

<br />
Xalmat, when did you last run HP regen tests on GoDS focused pets?<br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Eandori Raintree</a></b>
<br />
<a href="http://www.eqempyreal.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Empyreal</a> - Solusek Ro Server
<br />
</center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
